# Project Guidelines

> Read AGENTS.md at the root for the full guide. This rule file is a quick reference.

## Auth
- Server: `getServerUser()` from `@/lib/auth` — never read cookies manually.
- Client (web): `authClient` from `@/lib/auth-client`.
- Mobile: `authClient` from `@/lib/auth-client` (Expo SecureStore-backed).
- Redirect pattern: `if (!user) redirect('/signin?next=<path>')`.

## Database
- `dbQuery<T>()` → typed SELECT; `dbRun()` → INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE; `dbQueryOne<T>()` → first row.
- Always parameterise: `dbQuery('SELECT * FROM x WHERE id = $1', [id])`.
- App schema: `apps/web/src/lib/db/schema.ts`. Better Auth tables are managed by Better Auth.

## AI / Mastra
- Use `getMastraModel()` — never hard-code model strings.
- New agents → `apps/web/src/mastra/agents/` → register in `apps/web/src/mastra/index.ts`.
- Stream with `agent.stream()` → `createUIMessageStreamResponse`.

## Logging (Wide Events)
- One `console.log(JSON.stringify(event))` per API handler, in `finally`.
- Required fields: `route`, `timestamp`, `user_id`, `outcome`, `duration_ms`.
- Never use `console.log` for scattered debug strings.

## React Performance
- `Promise.all()` for parallel fetches — never sequential `await` for independent data.
- `next/dynamic` for heavy client components.
- Ternary (`a ? <A/> : <B/>`) not `&&` for conditional JSX.
- `React.memo` + `useCallback` on list item components.

## React Native
- NativeWind classes only — no inline style objects in list items.
- `expo-image` not RN `Image`.
- `<SafeAreaView>` from `react-native-safe-area-context`.
- Native deps in `apps/mobile/package.json` only.

## Security
- Never `NEXT_PUBLIC_` for DATABASE_URL or secrets.
- Validate request bodies with `zod`.
- Parameterised SQL always.

## Code Style
- Absolute imports (`@/lib/auth`) in web app.
- No barrel files — import from source.
- No comments that narrate code — only explain non-obvious intent.
